The '''Grand Dune''' located near [[Wikipedia:Nefta|Nefta]], [[Tunisia]], is the largest sand dune in the area. In [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] it served as the filming location for [[R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO]]'s landing in the [[Dune Sea]]. The film later returns to the site for a scene in which a few [[Desert stormtrooper|sandtroopers]] find the abandoned [[escape pod]] and traces of the fugitive [[droid]]s. The latter sequence was extended in the [[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Special Edition]] with shots from the [[Yuma|Yuma desert]].

